Fix round for the example site "__NAME__" in this repository (hwaro-examples).

An independent design review produced the findings below. Fix ALL of them.
Re-read the "__NAME__" entry in manifest.json, DESIGN.md §16, and the
AGENTS.md pattern library before starting.

FIX THE CLASS, NOT THE INSTANCE. Each finding names one element, but the rule
it cites (centered multi-line text, all-caps heading, off-palette code token,
clipped mobile element, …) is usually broken in more than one place. For every
finding, fix the element named AND sweep the whole site — templates, CSS,
content — for the same rule and fix every other occurrence in the same pass.
The reviewer re-audits the entire rendered surface; any instance you leave
behind fails the next round.

TRUST THE SYMPTOM, NOT THE PRESCRIPTION. A finding's "Fix:" line is the
reviewer's best guess and may point at a selector, value, or media-query block
that isn't in the code — or may already be satisfied. Reproduce the "Evidence:"
symptom first: if it's real, find its true cause in the rendered CSS and fix
that until "Accept:" passes; if you cannot reproduce it at all, treat the
finding as already satisfied and say so — never invent a change to match a
prescription you can't verify against the actual code.

__FINDINGS__

RULES: everything from the original build still applies — palette values
verbatim from the manifest, template idioms only from the AGENTS.md pattern
library, no emoji, no gradients beyond DESIGN.md caps, every href through
{{ base_url }}. Do not modify manifest.json. Do not git commit anything.

MANDATORY verification before reporting:
- cd examples/__NAME__ && hwaro build   (exit 0)
- the four DESIGN.md §15 step 9 greps are clean
  (including `grep -c '<h1' public/index.html` printing exactly 1)
- every acceptance criterion stated in the findings above passes — show the
  command output for each
- scripts/check-site.sh __NAME__   prints "PASS: __NAME__"

Report format: for each finding, one line stating what changed (file) and the
verification output that proves it. Then paste the check-site.sh output.
